, which could also be substituted for the Finnish cognate <b>Marttinen</b>.","French: shortened form of   Moreton   3."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Moreton was born in 1149, in Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England as the son of Lady Turet. He married Alice Haget in 1170, in Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 4 September 1194, in Wem, Shropshire, England, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1149–4 September 1194":"1149–4. september 1194","1149–1194":"1149–1194","1152–1247":"1152–1247","1170–1232":"1170–1232","1105–1157":"1105–1157","1149":"1149","1105":"1105","1247":"1247","1157":"1157","1232":"1232","1152":"1152","1194":"1194","1170":"1170","4 September 1194":"4. september 1194","Moreton, Cheshire, England":"Moreton, Cheshire, England","Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England":"Moreton Corbet, Shropshire, England","Wem, Shropshire, England":"Wem, Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"1149–4 September 1194":"1149–4. syyskuuta 1194","1149–1194":"1149–1194","1152–1247":"1152–1247","1170–1232":"1170–1232","1105–1157":"1105–1157","1149":"1149","1105":"1105","1247":"1247","1157":"1157","1232":"1232","1152":"1152","1194":"1194","1170":"1170","4 September 1194":"4. syyskuuta 1194","